data.title: Good in Green Bay
data.text: My son and I travelled to Green Bay from Ohio to take in a Packers game - after an 8+ hour drive and check in we were looking for dinner and had a nice experience here.  We started with a Bavarian Pretzel with a variety of dipping sauces as an appetizer.  I had the Spicy Elk Burger which was very tasty and the first time I had Elk - I especially enjoyed the cucumber salad side that came with it.  My son had The Noble Pig which he enjoyed as well. The only drawback was the portions seemed a little undersized.  Interestingly we had a server who said he was a beginner that had just started and that a more experienced person would keep an eye on things - however it was so busy that we only saw the "experienced" person once and the new guy did an excellent job of taking care of us. The only "problem" was the fact the Indians were playing in the playoffs at the time but no one would change the TV's from the Alabama football game - guess that happens when one is in a football only town.

data.title: Love the Roof Top Bar!
data.text: I've visited Titletown before but it was in the old railway station building (which I loved) but last night I visited again and this time it was the Roof Top Bar.  Wow, what a COOL PLACE!  Spacious and comfortable with (obviously) their great beer but also eats (I had pork tacos).  The view was very nice.  I really enjoyed my visit and can't wait to return again soon!

data.title: Great pre-game food!
data.text:
This was our first time to Green Bay for a game, glad we visited here. The place was packed and if you are like me, you want a hopping busy place to get you excited. The food was good with one item i'd pass on. Loved the artichoke dip, the mac'n'cheese pizza was great, but skip the Elk burger. Dry and flavorless. 

For a sweet treat, do the handcrafted soda's and try all 4, they're great.

data.title: A great place to celebrate Life!! Cheers!
data.text: The Titletown Brewery is housed in the old, now renovated, Chicago & Northwestern Train Depot. The Green Bay Packers use to travel from the depot back in the day to many of their away games. We enjoyed a delicious lunch. I had the elk sandwich and my wife the turkey cranberry on zucchini bread. Their chili, cheese, beer soup is to die for! Incredible!

data.title: Delicious food, unique atmosphere
data.text:
We spent the better part of the day touring Lambeau Field and The Hall Of Fame, then headed over to Titletown for beers and din-din.  Titletown has the brewery on one side if the street and the restaurant on the other side; the restaurant is in a rehabbed train station - cool.  I had their red ale which has a nice, full flavor and would be a good choice for folks who do not like a hoppy beer. 

We had the Poutine for the table. It was good, but just not my thing. Still, I would give it a try if it sounds good.  I had the Average Joe Burger for dinner. It was made very well and I particularly liked the Tomato Jam they put on it (I may just have to learn how to make it). Many if the options have jalapeños on them, which may be an issue for some, but there were still several options which did not have them. 

All in all, definitely worth a stop.

data.title: good food
data.text: It was very crowded when we walked in which is a great sign. They had good food and a decent selection of craft beers.

data.title: Great Food
data.text: A must while in Titletown! Great food and homemade beer. Try the beer/cheese soup. A must for your trip to Green Bay!

data.title: DMX has a Christmas album
data.text:
It's a true story.  The food is pretty good.
We do not recommend adding mustard to the lobster macaroni and cheese.

Mike knows the German candy website.  The pizza looked solid.  We generally liked the nachos.

Every person is born a boy.  It is incompetent dad's who make girls.

Priced reasonable, will return.

data.title: Packers/Colts!
data.text: Great place! Told we had 2 1/2 hour wait seated in 15 minutes in upstairs bar! Mike the bartender gave excellent service. The beers are great. Had cheese curds and fish tacos definitely try them. Root beer was also fantastic. Go here!!

data.title: Fun little dinner place
data.text: We got there around 5:30pm and they were alittle busy.  We were able to sit down at the bar or wait for a table.  We opted to go upstairs to the bar.  The bartender (short little brunette who was extremely fun/funny) was fabulous!!  She took our order, we ordered 2 plates, we told her we intended to split the meals.  When the food came, she had the kitchen split the dinners before they served us - very nice touch!  All in all, the food was great, the bartender was really a gem! Made for a fun visit

data.title: good eats
data.text: Wait staff was nice and informative. Food was really good, Plan to go back again and also take the brewery tour.

data.title: quick stop for a couple of beers and some curds.
data.text: Drove around town and checked out the sites.  Stopped for a beer and curds.  They and a good selection of beers and the curds were great the prices were fair.  Had a nice comfortable feel about the place.  A lot of locals were there.  Would go again.

data.title: Outstanding!
data.text: We were driving through Green Bay and looking for a new place to try.  This one had good reviews.  We were here during a packer game and it was exciting.  It is a very neat building.  I can say the turkey sandwhich on zucchini bread was by far the BEST sandwhich I have EVER had.  We will be back!

data.title: Lunch after Lambeau Tour
data.text:
Brought a small group of German students to Titletown after reading the great reviews it had on Tripadvisor. We ordered the nachos and cheese curd appetizer which everyone loved. 4 of us had the Strip steak dinner, some of us liked it, mine was completely fatty, honestly I am truly a picky steak eater, and this might be normal. The mashed potatoes were not that good either. It had a slight chemical taste. One of the students ordered the lobster mac and had a hard time finding the lobster. He also complained about the amount of cheese, too much?? I don't know, we are in Wisconsin, and we love cheese.
Another had a burger and she loved it. Another had ribs and he loved it. 
We all enjoyed the endless soda, and liked trying the flavors!

data.title: Fun, historic place with good food at reasonable prices!
data.text: This restaurant is situated in a cool, old train station.  The vibe is lively and it is fun to walk into a restaurant where everyone seems to be having a great time.  The food was particularly surprising.  I ordered the mussels and was impressed by the delicious preparation, the larger than usual size of the mussels and the large portion.  I was shocked to see such a large number of mussels, especially because I ordered the appetizer size.  My husband had the special of the day which was a creative pasta dish that he relished.  As the name implies, there was a nice variety of brews.  Service was friendly and efficient.

data.title: Great food at a great price
data.text: Delicious food and brews for very reasonable prices.  Great friendly servers and staff at this packed place.  Everything we has was excellent - you can't go wrong if you choose this place for a quick appetizer and beer or for dinner! We had cheese curds and burgers with salads - it was great.

data.title: Wedding reception
data.text: Relaxing atmosphere with an ambience of city, country feel about it. Open concept- lofty. Menu appealing. Home comforts

data.title: Fun place to visit
data.text: Good variety of beers and nice food options the staff were friendly and prompt with service. Must see place while in Green Bay

data.title: Nothing special
data.text:
Ate upstairs where decor was rundown and very plain.
Not a great atmosphere....back room had large party in it and was very noisy. 
Ordered pizza and waited a very long time for it.  Pizza was good but not worth the wait.
Wouldn't recommend....

data.title: Great burgers!
data.text: Titletown is a pub style restaurant with friendly service and very good beer and good. We had the Johnny blood red beer and loved it! We ate cheese curds and had burgers and they were delicious. There was a wait on the weekend but upstairs there is open seating so while we were waiting 1 hour to be seated, a table up stairs opened up and we ended up seated in 10 minutes! Definite Wisconsin place to dine!
